# Testing

## Requirements
- Use pytest + pytest-asyncio (`asyncio_mode = auto`)
- Test against real PostgreSQL (via `DATABASE_URL` or compose `db` service)
- No SQLite in-memory shortcuts — behavior must match production

## Structure
- `conftest.py` — shared fixtures (async client, db session, test app)
- One test file per module: `test_plants.py` for `app/services/plants.py`
- Name tests descriptively: `test_watering_streak_resets_after_missed_day`

## Do
- Use `httpx.AsyncClient` with `ASGITransport` for API tests
- Assert HTTP status codes and response schema shape

## Don't
- Commit secrets or real Telegram tokens in test files
- Skip tests for new features
- Mock the database unless testing external APIs (Telegram, ESP32)
